  <!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
  <div class="article">

    <!-- THE GAP -->
    <section class="cs-section reveal">
      <div class="cs-label">The Gap</div>
      <h2 class="cs-heading">PDFs don&rsquo;t ship products.</h2>

      <p class="cs-body">We&rsquo;d partnered with <strong>Ragged Edge</strong> &mdash; the London agency behind the
        Wise rebrand &mdash; on brand strategy and identity. Ten PDFs covering everything from verbal identity to motion
        design.</p>

      <p class="cs-body">The brand described how ZAR should <strong>feel</strong> &mdash; heavy, grounded, certain. How
        the UI should <strong>behave</strong> &mdash; anchored grids, stone textures, no glass effects. How motion
        should <strong>land</strong> &mdash; with the weight of rock, not the bounce of rubber.</p>

      <p class="cs-body">All of this existed as intent. None of it existed as code. My job was to close that gap.</p>

      <div class="cs-visual">
        <div class="cs-visual-inner">Brand PDFs (stacked) &rarr; gap &rarr; ZAR app on phone</div>
        <div class="cs-visual-caption">The distance between brand intent and production reality.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- BRAND VISION -->
    <section class="cs-section reveal">
      <div class="cs-label">The Brand Vision</div>
      <h2 class="cs-heading">A geological metaphor for money.</h2>

      <p class="cs-body">The brand isn&rsquo;t a fintech identity. It&rsquo;s an idea: <strong>money should feel
          solid</strong>. Like rock. Like something you can hold. This materializes as four UI principles:</p>

      <div class="cs-principle-grid">
        <div class="cs-principle-card">
          <div class="cs-principle-num">01</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-title">Structure</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-desc">Strict tectonic grid. Elements feel anchored. Nothing floats or drifts.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-principle-card">
          <div class="cs-principle-num">02</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-title">Physicality</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-desc">No glassy blurs or transparency. Solid and tangible. No lightweight aesthetics.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-principle-card">
          <div class="cs-principle-num">03</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-title">Rocks</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-desc">Stone textures on dollar bills and balances. Dollars look like they weigh
            something.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-principle-card">
          <div class="cs-principle-num">04</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-title">Haptics</div>
          <div class="cs-principle-desc">Roomy tap targets. Strong physical feedback. Not bouncy. Solid.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-visual">
        <div class="cs-visual-inner">Tectonic UI principles &mdash; visual examples from the app</div>
        <div class="cs-visual-caption">Four principles that govern every design decision in the system.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MINERAL PALETTE -->
    <section class="cs-section reveal">
      <div class="cs-label">The Palette</div>
      <h2 class="cs-heading">Colors named after minerals.</h2>

      <p class="cs-body">Not abstract variables. Geological names that carry the brand in every code reference. When an
        engineer writes <strong>Tanzanite/Core</strong> instead of <strong>blue500</strong>, they&rsquo;re speaking the
        brand language.</p>

      <div class="cs-mineral-row">
        <div class="cs-mineral-swatch">
          <div class="cs-mineral-circle" style="background: #D4A853;"></div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-name" style="color: #D4A853;">Gold</div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-use">Primary CTAs</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-mineral-swatch">
          <div class="cs-mineral-circle" style="background: #E8D5B0;"></div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-name" style="color: #b8a070;">Quartz</div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-use">Secondary</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-mineral-swatch">
          <div class="cs-mineral-circle" style="background: #5B8DEF;"></div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-name" style="color: #5B8DEF;">Tanzanite</div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-use">Info / Links</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-mineral-swatch">
          <div class="cs-mineral-circle" style="background: #4ADE80;"></div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-name" style="color: #2da55d;">Serpentine</div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-use">Success</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-mineral-swatch">
          <div class="cs-mineral-circle" style="background: #B1A8BD;"></div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-name" style="color: #8a7f98;">Amethyst</div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-use">Status</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-mineral-swatch">
          <div class="cs-mineral-circle" style="background: #C4BCB3;"></div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-name" style="color: #9a9289;">Limestone</div>
          <div class="cs-mineral-use">Neutrals</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="cs-body">Each family has a <strong>/Core</strong> value and numbered variants (100&ndash;600). 41 fill
        styles. 29 text styles. EK Modena Heavy for dollar amounts that feel immovable. Baikal for everything else.</p>

      <div class="cs-visual">
        <div class="cs-visual-inner">Full color token grid from Figma + typography scale</div>
        <div class="cs-visual-caption">41 fill styles, 29 text styles &mdash; every color named after a mineral.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="cs-divider"></div>

    <!-- BUILDING TECHTONIC -->
    <section class="cs-section reveal">
      <div class="cs-label">Building Techtonic</div>
      <h2 class="cs-heading">Token-first architecture.</h2>

      <p class="cs-body">I named the design system <strong>Techtonic</strong> &mdash; &ldquo;tech&rdquo; meets
        &ldquo;tectonic.&rdquo; The same geological metaphor encoded into every layer:</p>

      <div class="cs-arch-layers">
        <div class="cs-arch-layer">
          <div class="cs-arch-tag">LAYER 1</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-name">Tokens</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-desc">Colors, type, spacing, borders</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-arch-layer">
          <div class="cs-arch-tag">LAYER 2</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-name">Components</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-desc">Buttons, inputs, cards, sheets</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-arch-layer">
          <div class="cs-arch-tag">LAYER 3</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-name">Templates</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-desc">14 full-screen assemblies</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-arch-layer">
          <div class="cs-arch-tag">LAYER 4</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-name">Documentation</div>
          <div class="cs-arch-desc">Machine + human readable</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-stats">
        <div class="cs-stat">
          <div class="cs-stat-num">670+</div>
          <div class="cs-stat-label">Components</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-stat">
          <div class="cs-stat-num">37</div>
          <div class="cs-stat-label">Figma Pages</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-stat">
          <div class="cs-stat-num">41</div>
          <div class="cs-stat-label">Fill Styles</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-stat">
          <div class="cs-stat-num">29</div>
          <div class="cs-stat-label">Text Styles</div>
        </div>
        <div class="cs-stat">
          <div class="cs-stat-num">103</div>
