        </div>
        <div class="cs-stat">
          <div class="cs-stat-num">24K+</div>
          <div class="cs-stat-label">Lines of Code</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="cs-body">37 Figma pages with lifecycle management &mdash; active, deprecated, changelog, and a
        &ldquo;Future&rdquo; page for proposals. Everything versioned. Everything traceable.</p>

      <div class="cs-visual">
        <div class="cs-visual-inner">Techtonic Figma file overview &mdash; page structure and component inventory</div>
        <div class="cs-visual-caption">37 pages of organized, versioned, living design system.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MULTI-PLATFORM -->
    <section class="cs-section reveal">
      <div class="cs-label">Multi-Platform</div>
      <h2 class="cs-heading">One system. Three platforms.</h2>

      <p class="cs-body">Most design systems break when they cross platforms. Techtonic was built to ship everywhere.
      </p>

      <div class="cs-platform-grid">
        <div class="cs-platform-col">
          <div class="cs-platform-icon">&#x1F4F1;</div>
          <div class="cs-platform-name">Flutter</div>
