    <!-- THE MIGRATION -->
    <section class="cs-section reveal">
      <div class="cs-label">The Migration</div>
      <h2 class="cs-heading">Killing common_widgets.</h2>

      <p class="cs-body">Building a new system is half the work. Killing the old one is the other half. The inherited
        codebase had no documentation, no naming convention &mdash; just hex values scattered across files.</p>

      <p class="cs-body"><strong>Strategy: parallel run, then cut.</strong> New features used Techtonic exclusively.
        Existing screens migrated one at a time. When a component hit zero references &mdash; delete.</p>

      <div class="cs-migration-bar">
        <div class="cs-migration-labels">
          <div class="cs-migration-label old">common_widgets</div>
          <div class="cs-migration-label new">Techtonic</div>
